This paper deals with the interactions between adversarial attacks and neural network compression, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of compressed models to adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also explores the impact of compression on the transferability of adversarial samples, which is a topic that is relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
